# Union subtraction — `string | number | null` minus `null` leaves
# `string | number`. Demonstrates that negative narrowing on a union removes
# the tested member, and a second predicate then further narrows.
` { type: "(string | number | null) → string" }
to-string(x): if(x null?, "null", if(x number?, str(x), x))

result: to-string("hello")
